  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "mx6ioMQzzonMGAueN9+ycdTINKQ=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## `adapter/src/channel/` layout\n\n```\nadapter/src/channel/\n  index.ts                    - Public exports\n  composite-factory.ts        - Routes \"gql\"/\"swarm\" to sub-factories\n  swarm-channel.ts            - IChannel: outbox push + inbox pull\n  swarm-channel-factory.ts    - Creates SwarmChannel from ChannelConfig\n  create-composite-factory.ts - createSwarmSyncBuilder() for ReactorBuilder.withSync()\n  register-swarm-channel.ts   - Runtime factory injection (legacy/edge cases)\n  add-swarm-remote.ts         - Per-drive Swarm remote registration\n  manifest-manager.ts         - User + drive manifest writes\n```\n\n### How they fit\n\n- `swarm-channel.ts` is the new code path \u2014 a native `IChannel` implementation that SyncManager treats identically to the GQL channel.\n- `composite-factory.ts` plus `create-composite-factory.ts` form the wiring that lets GQL and Swarm coexist behind one factory.\n- `add-swarm-remote.ts` is the entry point used by plugin init / registration retry to attach a Swarm remote to a specific drive.\n- `manifest-manager.ts` is the only module that writes the user and drive manifest feeds, keeping manifest-write logic in one place.\n- `register-swarm-channel.ts` exists for edge cases where the factory needs to be injected after reactor construction (legacy paths).",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:28.000Z"
    }
  },
